headline: Intel's Struggles Continue, but Is a Turnaround Near?
summary: Intel's (NASDAQ: INTC) first-quarter results came up flat, and investors sent shares of the struggling semiconductor company lower.  Intel shares are down more than 40% over the past year.  The lackluster numbers easily surpassed the $0.01 in EPS and $12.3 billion in revenue in the analyst consensus compiled by LSEG, but Intel's guidance disappointed.
